This paper is primarily focused on optimization techniques for deep learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the dynamics of distributed systems, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper introduces a new optimization procedure that could be considered an artificial intelligence technique (cs.AI). The use of Lagrangian mechanics and energy concepts could also be relevant to the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) or systems and control (cs.SY).
